OL,3,C'My father's death was not
OL,4,Cinevitable', says son of infected
OL,5,Cblood victim
OL,7,F"They were given money randomly
OL,8,Fthroughout the 1990s and he was given
OL,9,Fpayments for the HIV in his later
OL,10,Flife, because he couldn't work and so
OL,11,Fon, but never compensation in the
OL,12,Fsense of 'we've done something wrong,
OL,13,Fhere's your compensation for our
OL,14,Fmisdoings'."
OL,16,FIt is estimated that more than 400
OL,17,Fpeople in Wales were given
OL,18,Fcontaminated blood and blood products.
