OL,3,C'My father's death was not
OL,4,Cinevitable', says son of infected
OL,5,Cblood victim
OL,7,F"They had warnings from the World
OL,8,FHealth Organisation, I think back to
OL,9,Fthe late 1940s, definitely early
OL,10,F1950s, that pooling blood products was
OL,11,Fnot a good idea due to the risk of
OL,12,Fhepatitis - obviously they didn't know
OL,13,Fabout HIV then - so really it wasn't
OL,14,Finevitable that his treatment was
OL,15,Feventually going to kill him.
OL,17,F"People did wrong things and made
OL,18,Fwrong decisions and bad decisions for
OL,19,Fwhatever reason."
